# Aakanksha Naik | Semantic Scholar

[

## Stress Test Evaluation for Natural Language Inference

](/paper/Stress-Test-Evaluation-for-Natural-Language-Naik-Ravichander/175b58fe7e49bb5c0c771b73f8834bcff21b59c7)

[Aakanksha Naik](/author/Aakanksha-Naik/23175870)[Abhilasha Ravichander](/author/Abhilasha-Ravichander/3023068)[N. Sadeh](/author/N.-Sadeh/2464164)[C. Rosé](/author/C.-Ros%C3%A9/35959897)[Graham Neubig](/author/Graham-Neubig/1700325)

Computer Science

-   2 June 2018

This work proposes an evaluation methodology consisting of automatically constructed “stress tests” that allow us to examine whether systems have the ability to make real inferential decisions, and reveals strengths and weaknesses of these models with respect to challenging linguistic phenomena.

[

## OLMo: Accelerating the Science of Language Models

](/paper/OLMo%3A-Accelerating-the-Science-of-Language-Models-Groeneveld-Beltagy/ac45bbf9940512d9d686cf8cd3a95969bc313570)

[Dirk Groeneveld](/author/Dirk-Groeneveld/3458736)[Iz Beltagy](/author/Iz-Beltagy/2260133345) [Hanna Hajishirzi](/author/Hanna-Hajishirzi/2264251662)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   1 February 2024

OLMo is built, a competitive, truly Open Language Model, to enable the scientific study of language models and it is hoped this release will empower the open research community and inspire a new wave of innovation.

[

## Dolma: an Open Corpus of Three Trillion Tokens for Language Model Pretraining Research

](/paper/Dolma%3A-an-Open-Corpus-of-Three-Trillion-Tokens-for-Soldaini-Kinney/ad1bb59e3e18a0dd8503c3961d6074f162baf710)

[Luca Soldaini](/author/Luca-Soldaini/3328733)[Rodney Kinney](/author/Rodney-Kinney/2282136328) [Kyle Lo](/author/Kyle-Lo/46258841)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   31 January 2024

To facilitate scientific research on language model pretraining, Dolma is curate and released, a three-trillion-token English corpus built from a diverse mixture of web content, scientific papers, code, public-domain books, social media, and encyclopedic materials.

[

## EQUATE: A Benchmark Evaluation Framework for Quantitative Reasoning in Natural Language Inference

](/paper/EQUATE%3A-A-Benchmark-Evaluation-Framework-for-in-Ravichander-Naik/1eff94b44432a8e6af29288b8234494516579ad3)

[Abhilasha Ravichander](/author/Abhilasha-Ravichander/3023068)[Aakanksha Naik](/author/Aakanksha-Naik/23175870)[C. Rosé](/author/C.-Ros%C3%A9/35959897)[E. Hovy](/author/E.-Hovy/144547315)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   11 January 2019

Equal (Evaluating Quantitative Understanding Aptitude in Textual Entailment), a new framework for quantitative reasoning in textual entailment, is presented and it is found that on average, state-of-the-art methods do not achieve an absolute improvement over a majority-class baseline, suggesting that they do not implicitly learn to reason with quantities.

[

## TDDiscourse: A Dataset for Discourse-Level Temporal Ordering of Events

](/paper/TDDiscourse%3A-A-Dataset-for-Discourse-Level-Temporal-Naik-Breitfeller/5b58058af2a598d3a753d073c252cdfc6fad4286)

[Aakanksha Naik](/author/Aakanksha-Naik/23175870)[Luke Breitfeller](/author/Luke-Breitfeller/113477466)[C. Rosé](/author/C.-Ros%C3%A9/35959897)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   1 September 2019

This work creates TDDiscourse, the first dataset focusing specifically on temporal links between event pairs which are more than one sentence apart, by augmenting TimeBank-Dense, a corpus of English news articles, manually annotating global pairs that cannot be inferred automatically from existing annotations.

[

## Exploring Numeracy in Word Embeddings

](/paper/Exploring-Numeracy-in-Word-Embeddings-Naik-Ravichander/a5dde0a71fb0465d33b95496c4bb64914b3d62d9)

[Aakanksha Naik](/author/Aakanksha-Naik/23175870)[Abhilasha Ravichander](/author/Abhilasha-Ravichander/3023068)[C. Rosé](/author/C.-Ros%C3%A9/35959897)[E. Hovy](/author/E.-Hovy/144547315)

Mathematics, Linguistics

-   1 July 2019

Inspired by cognitive studies on how humans perceive numbers, an analysis framework is developed to test how well word embeddings capture two essential properties of numbers: magnitude and numeration.

[

## Towards Open Domain Event Trigger Identification using Adversarial Domain Adaptation

](/paper/Towards-Open-Domain-Event-Trigger-Identification-Naik-Ros'e/97d3c0a402097a8c03ed66bd0e73ac4d4ac70b31)

[Aakanksha Naik](/author/Aakanksha-Naik/23175870)[C. Ros'e](/author/C.-Ros'e/73771627)

Computer Science

-   22 May 2020

This work leverages the adversarial domain adaptation (ADA) framework to introduce domain-invariance and preliminary experiments reveal that finetuning on 1% labeled data, followed by self-training leads to substantial improvement, reaching 51.5 and 67.2 F1 on literature and news respectively.

[

## Literature-Augmented Clinical Outcome Prediction

](/paper/Literature-Augmented-Clinical-Outcome-Prediction-Naik-Parasa/a6967ee51832f16c5cae8f18bfa84a9832776aab)

[Aakanksha Naik](/author/Aakanksha-Naik/23175870)[S. Parasa](/author/S.-Parasa/5939166)[Sergey Feldman](/author/Sergey-Feldman/46411828)[Lucy Lu Wang](/author/Lucy-Lu-Wang/31860505)[Tom Hope](/author/Tom-Hope/2041698667)

Medicine, Computer Science

NAACL-HLT

-   16 November 2021

This work develops methods to retrieve literature based on noisy, information-dense patient notes, and to augment existing outcome prediction models with retrieved papers in a manner that maximizes predictive accuracy.

[

## Tackling Biomedical Text Summarization: OAQA at BioASQ 5B

](/paper/Tackling-Biomedical-Text-Summarization%3A-OAQA-at-5B-Chandu-Naik/4a98f2a34cb5e39533c57fe0ed0ac0c9854394d3)

[Khyathi Raghavi Chandu](/author/Khyathi-Raghavi-Chandu/37619618)[Aakanksha Naik](/author/Aakanksha-Naik/23175870)[A. Chandrasekar](/author/A.-Chandrasekar/47387170)[Zi Yang](/author/Zi-Yang/2111906048)[Niloy Gupta](/author/Niloy-Gupta/2387633)[Eric Nyberg](/author/Eric-Nyberg/144287919)

Computer Science, Medicine

-   2017

This paper describes its participation in phase B of task 5b of the fifth edition of the annual BioASQ challenge, which includes answering factoid, list, yes-no and summary questions from biomedical data and proposes a novel word embedding based tf-idf similarity metric and a soft positional constraint which improve the system performance.

[

## On-the-fly Definition Augmentation of LLMs for Biomedical NER

](/paper/On-the-fly-Definition-Augmentation-of-LLMs-for-NER-Munnangi-Feldman/cc13d65f00d02c6fc01fc996a10e7bc503e3deec)

[Monica Munnangi](/author/Monica-Munnangi/2294363095)[Sergey Feldman](/author/Sergey-Feldman/2294364786)[Byron C. Wallace](/author/Byron-C.-Wallace/2306260315)[Silvio Amir](/author/Silvio-Amir/2294355004)[Tom Hope](/author/Tom-Hope/2266841339)[Aakanksha Naik](/author/Aakanksha-Naik/23175870)

Computer Science, Medicine

-   29 March 2024

It is found that careful prompting strategies also improve LLM performance, allowing them to outperform fine-tuned language models in few-shot settings, and definition augmentation is useful for both open source and closed LLMs.
